items.comment: (BorderBetweenPolitiesFn GEO-1 GEO-2) applied to two GeopoliticalEntitys returns the entire intangible Border (if any) that separates their territories. The border returned by BorderBetweenPolitiesFn may be discontinuous (such as the border between France and Spain, interrupted by Andorra), or circular (such as the border between Italy and San Marino), or in abnormal cases it may even have multiple disconnected and nested cyclic fragments (the border between Belgium and Netherlands, due to the Baarle-Nassau and Baarle-Hartog enclaves), or move back and forth periodically (such as at the Isle des Faisans). In any case, (BorderBetweenPolitiesFn GEO-1 GEO-2) must denote exactly one object (if it denotes at all) since BorderBetweenPolitiesFn is a function. BorderBetweenPolitiesFn is undefined for pairs of GeopoliticalEntitys whose territories do not actually share a border, such as Albania and UnitedStatesOfAmerica. See also politiesBorderEachOther, assertions using that predicate express a necessary and sufficient condition on the entities involved returning a value with this function and BorderBetweenFn which defines the border between two GeographicalRegions.

(BurntFn TYPE) is the specialization of TYPE consisting of all burnt instances of TYPE. For example, (BurntFn Toast) is the collection of slices of burnt toast and (BurntFn Skin) is the collection of regions burnt skin. Note that if a given instance of TYPE becomes so completely burned that it is no longer an instance of TYPE (but is, say, a portion of ash), then it will _not_ be an instance of (BurntFn TYPE).

items.comment: (CityGridSectionFn ST1 ST2 ST3 ST4) denotes the unique, roughly rectangular urban region (if any) that is completely bounded by segments of each of the streets ST1 - ST4. The relative order (but not the absolute positions) of the arguments here is important: it should be physically possible to circle completely the bounded area once by starting along ST1 and making successive right-hand turns on ST2, ST3, ST4, and back onto ST1. The bounded area must be part of a region that has a GridStreetSystem running through it. To have this function return a given street-bounded rectangular city section SECTION, one can fill its arg1 position with any of the four streets that borders SECTION, and then continue to fill in the remaining argument-places according to the order in which one would travel along the other three streets if one were circling SECTION in a clockwise fashion (i.e. by making only right-hand turns). See also CitySectionFn and CityBlockFn.
label: City Grid Section Fn
CityGridSectionFn

label: Bram Stoker
BramStoker
items.comment: Bram (Abraham) Stoker was born November 8, 1847 in Dublin, Ireland. Stoker was a sickly child and spent a lot of time in bed. Growing up his mother told him a lot of horror stories. Stoker studied Math at Trinity College Dublin. After graduation he became a civil servant. At this time, he also worked as a free lance journalist, a drama critic and editor of the "Evening Mail". In 1876 he met Sir Henry Irving, a famous actor. Stoker accepted a job as a personal secretary to Irving and went to England in 1878. While working for Irving he met an aspiring actress named Florence Balcombe. They were married 1878 and had one son, Noel, born 1879. In England he also began writing a series of novels and short stories the first of which was "The Snake's Pass". Although best known for Dracula_TheNovel, Stoker wrote eighteen books before he died in 1912 of exhaustion

label: Brandenburg v. Ohio
BrandenburgVTheStateOfOhio-CourtCase
items.comment: An important case concerning USCitizensRightToFreedomOfSpeech. The particulars were that ClarenceBrandenburg, a member of the Ku Klux Klan, was taped at an Ohio Klan rally making numerous racist remarks, burning a cross, and accusing the (GovernmentFn UnitedStatesOfAmerica) of suppressing Caucasians. He was convicted under Ohio's Criminal Syndicalism statute for advocating violence, and his appeal to state appellate court was dismissed. The UnitedStatesSupremeCourt struck down the law under which Brandenburg was convicted on the grounds that only speech which threatened to induce 'imminent lawless action' could be proscribed, given first amendment protections (the ImminentLawlessActionPrinciple). This ruling placed considerable strictures on the ClearAndPresentDangerPrinciple enunciated by OliverWendellHolmesJr some 50 years before.

items.comment: For any given movement type TYPE, (BlockedForFn TYPE) is the attribute of instances of Path_Customary that are blocked for movements of the type TYPE (from end to end). For example, (holdsIn TIME (pathState PATH (BlockedForFn (TransportViaFn Truck)))) means that during TIME, PATH is blocked for transportation through PATH (from end to end) via trucks. Note that when (pathState PATH (BlockedForFn (TransportViaFn Truck))) is true during TIME, it says nothing about whether, during TIME, PATH is blocked or open (see OpenForFn) for any other kind movement of transportation on PATH. Note also that (pathState PATH (BlockedForFn TYPE)) does not imply that no movement of the type TYPE is on PATH---it simply means that there is no movement of the type TYPE whose objectMoving can get one end from the other through the entire PATH.

items.label: Buddha
items.comment: Also known as SiddharthaGautama. Born: c.563, Died: c.483 B.C. in Nepal. A soothsayer is said to have predicted at Siddhartha's birth that he would become a world ruler or a world teacher. His father, King Suddhodana, of the warrior caste, raised him in great luxury, but at the age of 29 Siddhartha renounced the world to become a wandering ascetic and search for a solution to the problems of death and human suffering. After six years of spiritual discipline, he achieved supreme enlightenment at the age of 35 while meditating under a pipal tree at Bodh Gaya. He spent the rest of his life teaching his doctrines and establishing a community of monks, the #$Sangha, to continue his work.

An instance of both PartialFunction and BinaryFunction. When applied to instances REG1 and REG2 of GeographicalRegion, BorderBetweenFn returns the entire Border (if any) that separates REG1 and REG2.

For instance, (BorderBetweenFn (TerritoryFn France) (TerritoryFn Germany)) is the entire border between (TerritoryFn France) and (TerritoryFn Germany).

Note that the border returned by BorderBetweenFn may be discontinuous (such as the border between France and Spain, interrupted by Andorra), or circular (such as the border between Italy and San Marino), or in abnormal cases it may even have multiple disconnected and nested cyclic fragments (e.g., the border between Belgium and the Netherlands, due to the Baarle-Nassau and Baarle-Hartog enclaves), or move back and forth periodically (such as at the Isle des Faisans). Note also that BorderBetweenFn is undefined for pairs of regions that do not actually share a border, such as (TerritoryFn France) and (TerritoryFn UnitedStatesOfAmerica). See also borderBetweenRegions, which is a (canonically) corresponding predicate for this function.

items.comment: China, governed as the Peoples' Republic of China (PRC), is a country which claims to be the government of all of China. Taiwan_RepublicOfChina (ROC) also makes this claim. China_PeoplesRepublic controls all of China except Taiwan Province on the Island of Formosa [Formosa_Island] (or 'Taiwan') and QuemoyIsland and MatsuIsland of Fujian Province a few kilometers off the coast. China borders on the EastChinaSea and the SouthChinaSea. If a single instance of SubLRealNumber is put in the argument position to this function, it returns a precise quantity of bits (which is an instance of ComputerMemoryCapacity). If two SubLRealNumbers are put in the argument position, it returns an interval (which is an instance of ComputerMemoryCapacity). Thus, (Bit NUM) denotes a particular quantity of binary bits. (Bit NUM1 NUM2) returns a range of binary bits. See also Byte, Megabyte.

(CenterFn OBJ) denotes the point at the spatial center of an object. Formally, this can be defined as a point such that the average of the distances from this point to all points which are 'in' (see spatiallySubsumes) OBJ is minimized. Note that for objects whose density is not homogeneous (CenterFn OBJ) may be different from the 'center of gravity' of the object. Also, for objects which aren't spatially continuous (see SpatiallyContinuousThing), (CenterFn OBJ) is not necessarily 'in' (see spatiallySubsumes) OBJ. For example, the centroid of a non-spatially-continuous object such as a flock of seagulls is not necessarily a point in one of the seagulls.

items.comment: A function and an instance of UnitOfComputerStorageCapacity, representing a common unit of computer memory and disk capacity, consisting typically of 8 Bits. Like all instances of UnitOfMeasure, its arity is variable between one and two, and its arguments must be instances of SubLRealNumber. If a single instance of SubLRealNumber is put in the argument position to this function, it returns a precise quantity of bytes (which is an instance of ComputerMemoryCapacity). If two SubLRealNumbers are put in the argument position, it returns an interval (which is an instance of ComputerMemoryCapacity). Thus, (Byte NUM) denotes a particular quantity of bytes. Christian Trinity
ChristianTrinity
items.comment: The holy trinity in Christian theology. This is a very vexing concept, and any representation is likely to incur the wrath of some group of zealots and be considered heretical. In this representation I assume a heretical partonomic structure from the outset, and establish the trinity as a group of three divine beings, namely: GodTheFather, GodTheSon, and GodTheHolyGhost. Note that much theological thought on the subject claims that the trinity is not a part-whole structure -- each member is simultaneously a member of, and identical to, the trinity as a whole. I'm not convinced that Cyc (currently) needs a more complex definition than the one offered here for common-sense reasoning in a general (i.e., non-expert) fashion.
